---
name: js-effect-multishot-long-fold
backends: [int, js]
---

# Multi-shot effect result folded with a Long accumulator (js-effect-multishot-in-while-loop)

Regression for `js-effect-multishot-in-while-loop`: the JsGen CPS codegen lowered an
effectful `foldLeft(0L)((acc, x) => acc + x.toLong)` (running under a `handle` block, so
the fold body is CPS-lowered) with a **raw** JS `+`. Because a `Long` seed is a JS BigInt
and the list elements are plain Numbers, the emitted `(acc + _t)` threw at runtime with
"Cannot mix BigInt and other types". The CPS `ApplyInfix` path now mirrors the non-CPS
path and routes any not-provably-Int arithmetic through the BigInt-aware `_arith`.

```scalascript
multi effect NonDet:
  def choose(options: List[Int]): Int

def program(): Int ! NonDet =
  val a = NonDet.choose(List(1, 2, 3))
  val b = NonDet.choose(List(10, 20))
  a + b

def workload(): Long =
  var total = 0L
  var i = 0
  while i < 2 do
    val all = handle(program()) {
      case NonDet.choose(opts, resume) => opts.flatMap(opt => resume(opt))
    }
    total = total + all.foldLeft(0L)((acc, x) => acc + x.toLong)
    i = i + 1
  total

println(workload())
```
